1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,300
<i> He's my ex.</i>

2
00:00:01,467 --> 00:00:02,533
<i>I wasn't seeing you
at the same time.</i>

3
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:03,400
<i> I dated him first.</i>

4
00:00:03,533 --> 00:00:05,833
<i>Dad saved me
from my old life.</i>

5
00:00:05,967 --> 00:00:07,867
<i>I never want to
go back there.</i>

6
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,467
<i>- Why didn't you tell me?
- [HORN HONKING]</i>

7
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:11,300
<i> Gio, I love you so much.</i>

8
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:13,067
<i> I could never do that to you.</i>

9
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:15,300
<i>- And this is Mr. Andy--
- Arellano.</i>

10
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,567
<i>The world of entrepreneurs
like us is very small.</i>

11
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,867
<i> Yes, Mr. Lucero.</i>

12
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,100
<i> Is there a problem?</i>

13
00:00:20,233 --> 00:00:21,300
<i>You don't have a
good reputation</i>

14
00:00:21,433 --> 00:00:22,567
<i> when it comes to business.</i>

15
00:00:22,700 --> 00:00:26,133
<i>I won't get into this venture
if he's involved.</i>

16
00:00:26,267 --> 00:00:27,733
<i> No matter what happens,</i>

17
00:00:27,867 --> 00:00:29,933
<i> don't say anything.</i>

18
00:00:30,067 --> 00:00:31,367
<i> I need you, Sandro.</i>

19
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,633
<i>There are people
trying to infiltrate Hotel 88.</i>

20
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,467
<i> We can't let them succeed.</i>

21
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,767
<i>You need to act
before it's too late.</i>

22
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:44,733
<i>Either Uncle Ronald
or Andy Arellano.</i>

23
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:46,433
<i> We have to pick one.</i>

24
00:00:46,567 --> 00:00:49,133
<i>We'll hurt Luna if
we go against them.</i>

25
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:56,100
Me or them?

26
00:00:57,600 --> 00:01:00,733
Uncle Andy, are you sure
we can't change your mind?

27
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:03,100
I'm sorry, Luna, but no.

28
00:01:03,233 --> 00:01:04,733
I know Ronald Lucero

29
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:07,100
and I know he doesn't like me.

30
00:01:07,267 --> 00:01:09,700
And honestly,
I don't like him either.

31
00:01:09,833 --> 00:01:13,033
But you've already settled
the hotel's debt with the bank.

32
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:14,533
You're right about that.

33
00:01:16,067 --> 00:01:19,167
Uh, Luna, I'm not trying
to pressure you, okay?

34
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:22,433
But just so you know,
if you don't choose me,

35
00:01:22,567 --> 00:01:26,767
I'll expect you to repay me
as soon as possible.

36
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:27,967
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY]
Okay.

37
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:29,700
You have my word,
Uncle Andy.

38
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:32,400
You'll be Hotel 88's partner.

39
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:34,767
You're not Dad's friend
for nothing.

40
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,500
I will talk to them.

41
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,067
Good.

42
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,767
- Thank you, Luna.
- Thank you, Uncle Andy.

43
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,200
Leon.

44
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,200
We need to talk.

45
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:54,333
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

46
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:07,300
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

47
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,367
Let me see yours, Boyet.

48
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:05,267
This is something
I will never forget.

49
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:10,867
Every morning, I eat
breakfast with my parents.

50
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,500
Very good.

51
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:17,200
A family that eats together
stays together.

52
00:03:17,333 --> 00:03:19,167
- Yes.
- [JADE CHUCKLES]

53
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,867
What about you, Kimmy?
What did you paint?

54
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:24,667
I painted my birthday party.

55
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,900
Wow!

56
00:03:27,033 --> 00:03:28,200
Very good, Kimmy!

57
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:31,733
Birthdays are the best,
aren't they?

58
00:03:31,867 --> 00:03:33,633
What about you, Jade?

59
00:03:33,767 --> 00:03:35,000
What's your painting?

60
00:03:35,133 --> 00:03:36,833
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Well...

61
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:39,567
It's my birthday too.

62
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:42,100
[KIMMY] What are you doing
in your painting?

63
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,300
[JADE GIGGLES]

64
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:44,733
I was a kid here.

65
00:03:44,867 --> 00:03:49,633
This was the first time
I saw snow in Japan.

66
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:52,433
You must've been so happy,
Jade.

67
00:03:52,567 --> 00:03:54,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

68
00:03:54,700 --> 00:03:55,667
I was so happy.

69
00:03:55,800 --> 00:04:00,667
[KIMMY] But there's
no snow in the Philippines.

70
00:04:01,433 --> 00:04:06,800
So are you going to leave us

71
00:04:06,933 --> 00:04:08,500
to see the snow?

72
00:04:08,633 --> 00:04:11,300
Of course not.
I would never leave you.

73
00:04:11,433 --> 00:04:14,100
I want to go back one day.

74
00:04:14,233 --> 00:04:16,133
And when that day
comes,

75
00:04:16,267 --> 00:04:20,333
I will be the happiest girl
in the world.

76
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:24,333
I want to experience snow again
with all of you.

77
00:04:24,467 --> 00:04:27,333
That's impossible, Jade.

78
00:04:28,033 --> 00:04:28,733
Hmm?

79
00:04:28,867 --> 00:04:31,700
Who knows?
Anything is possible.

80
00:04:31,833 --> 00:04:38,733
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

81
00:04:38,867 --> 00:04:40,600
[HENRI] Jeffrey Tanyag.

82
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:42,167
Sandro Soliman.

83
00:04:42,300 --> 00:04:43,767
Peter Montevilla.

84
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:46,767
[MARINA]
Benjamin "Bok" dela Rosa.

85
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:48,667
This one's worse.

86
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,033
He's not missing.

87
00:04:50,167 --> 00:04:51,600
He was found dead.

88
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:54,133
[SIGHS]

89
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:57,633
They were all last seen
at Hotel 88.

90
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:00,633
That can't be a coincidence.

91
00:05:02,733 --> 00:05:07,633
And not a single one of them
has been found yet.

92
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,933
[SIGHS SHARPLY]
What is up with that hotel?

93
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:15,767
Ever since Michael
and Federico died...

94
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:19,967
a lot of things have happened
that we don't understand.

95
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:23,600
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

96
00:05:23,733 --> 00:05:26,233
In all my years on this island,

97
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:29,100
I've never felt this...

98
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:31,000
lost.

99
00:05:31,133 --> 00:05:37,933
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

100
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:39,733
If you'll let me...

101
00:05:41,467 --> 00:05:42,967
I want to lead the case.

102
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:47,433
So you can focus on
your other tasks.

103
00:05:47,567 --> 00:05:50,867
We can't let our world
revolve around Hotel 88.

104
00:05:53,033 --> 00:05:55,367
- [SIGHS SOFTLY]
- That is...

105
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:59,200
...if you think
I can handle this.

106
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:06,367
[CURIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

107
00:06:17,167 --> 00:06:18,967
So, Leon...

108
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,833
What do you really want to say?

109
00:06:20,967 --> 00:06:22,833
Spit it out already.

110
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:27,067
How did you and Dad
become friends?

111
00:06:31,033 --> 00:06:32,700
[ANDY SIGHS]

112
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:35,300
Seriously?

113
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,800
You brought me
all the way out here

114
00:06:37,933 --> 00:06:39,300
just to ask me that?

115
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:42,133
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

116
00:06:42,300 --> 00:06:43,467
Is there something wrong
with my question?

117
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:48,167
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

118
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:50,433
Business, Leon.

119
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:53,633
There are only a handful
of businessmen on the island.

120
00:06:53,767 --> 00:06:55,100
That's how I met your father.

121
00:06:55,233 --> 00:06:56,400
You know, we...

122
00:06:56,533 --> 00:06:58,067
We move in the same circles.

123
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:03,533
[SIGHS] Does that
answer your question?

124
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:09,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

125
00:07:09,967 --> 00:07:10,900
But, uh...

126
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:12,400
[CHUCKLES]

127
00:07:12,533 --> 00:07:14,100
You and I both know...

128
00:07:15,467 --> 00:07:18,233
that's not what you
really want to ask me.

129
00:07:18,367 --> 00:07:21,433
So, ask away.

130
00:07:21,567 --> 00:07:23,067
I'll answer everything.

131
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:24,967
Everything?

132
00:07:25,100 --> 00:07:26,200
Everything.

133
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,833
I have nothing to hide from you.

134
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,900
What are your intentions
with the hotel?

135
00:07:33,033 --> 00:07:34,033
To help.

136
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:37,500
In case you've forgotten,

137
00:07:37,633 --> 00:07:39,367
your sister came to me.

138
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,833
You really need help
here at Hotel 88,

139
00:07:41,967 --> 00:07:43,767
and I'm just here
to provide it.

140
00:07:44,833 --> 00:07:45,900
What else?

141
00:07:46,033 --> 00:07:47,067
Give it to me straight.

142
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:50,833
Leon, uh...

143
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:54,233
I don't like your tone.

144
00:07:54,367 --> 00:07:55,533
What do you want?

145
00:07:56,400 --> 00:07:58,067
I want to know the truth.

146
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:00,333
I'm a greedy man!

147
00:08:00,467 --> 00:08:01,867
Hmm?

148
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,567
That's the truth.

149
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:06,100
I don't like
competition in business.

150
00:08:07,167 --> 00:08:08,733
And Hotel 88?

151
00:08:08,867 --> 00:08:10,667
This is just business,
Leon.

152
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,733
And now the
smartest decision I can make

153
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,200
from a businessman's
point of view

154
00:08:14,333 --> 00:08:15,933
is to partner with you!

155
00:08:16,067 --> 00:08:19,267
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

156
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:20,667
Now...

157
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:26,700
Now, you don't have
any other questions?

158
00:08:27,633 --> 00:08:29,067
I'll go ahead then.

159
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:40,533
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

160
00:08:46,433 --> 00:08:47,600
Hey!

161
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:50,200
Be careful! You might get hurt!

162
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,167
[CHUCKLES]

163
00:08:55,833 --> 00:08:57,400
Why are you smiling?

164
00:08:57,400 --> 00:08:58,900
Is there something funny?

165
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,400
Is it me?

166
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,667
[SNORTS]

167
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:03,400
I'm just happy.

168
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:04,700
About what?

169
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,833
Because you're happy.

170
00:09:12,867 --> 00:09:13,967
Hmm.

171
00:09:13,967 --> 00:09:16,400
My happiness
is actually quite simple.

172
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:22,567
[JADE] Just seeing them happy
makes me twice as happy.

173
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,867
Okay.

174
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,400
What do you mean?

175
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,933
I know how to make that smile
on your lips permanent.

176
00:09:36,533 --> 00:09:38,533
What are you talking about?

177
00:09:38,533 --> 00:09:40,600
[MIMICS] What are you
talking about?

178
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,867
Whatever.

179
00:09:42,867 --> 00:09:44,000
Edward.

180
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:45,633
You're going crazy again.

181
00:09:46,733 --> 00:09:48,733
I've been crazy for a long time.

182
00:09:48,733 --> 00:09:53,633
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:09:53,633 --> 00:09:54,700
For you.

184
00:09:55,967 --> 00:09:59,900
[CHILDREN GUSHING]

185
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,767
[JADE] Hey!

186
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:03,900
You guys are doing too much!

187
00:10:03,900 --> 00:10:05,667
- [CHILDREN GUSHING]
- Hey, that's enough!

188
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,367
You too? C'mon!

189
00:10:07,367 --> 00:10:10,267
Put all your paint away!

190
00:10:10,667 --> 00:10:12,700
- [GUSHING]
- Go ahead! You're crazy!

191
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,533
[MIMICS] You're crazy!

192
00:10:16,567 --> 00:10:17,800
For you.

193
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:26,300
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

194
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,767
Today is Tuesday.

195
00:10:29,467 --> 00:10:30,733
Yes, you're right.

196
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:32,933
Jade is in the community.

197
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,767
You've been waiting for her,
haven't you?

198
00:10:37,033 --> 00:10:39,767
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

199
00:10:39,767 --> 00:10:41,500
Even though you haven't
talked for a long time,

200
00:10:41,500 --> 00:10:43,267
you're still close, aren't you?

201
00:10:43,867 --> 00:10:45,867
Your friendship
is really something else.

202
00:10:47,900 --> 00:10:49,600
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

203
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,567
Jade and I were
always best friends.

204
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,500
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

205
00:10:54,500 --> 00:10:57,733
Unless you won't admit
that you have feelings for her,

206
00:10:58,567 --> 00:11:00,667
she'll continue seeing you
as a friend.

207
00:11:00,667 --> 00:11:06,433
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

208
00:11:06,433 --> 00:11:08,467
That's all I'll ever be to her.

209
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:10,633
[SIGHS]

210
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,767
Oh, look!

211
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:18,000
The person you've been
waiting for is finally here.

212
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:20,733
She's here.

213
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:29,000
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

214
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,433
- [JADE] Kiko.
- Hey, Jade.

215
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,667
Why are you here?

216
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:39,367
Monette said you're
in the community

217
00:11:39,367 --> 00:11:42,533
[JADE] Oh, no. I wanted to
go home with my sister.

218
00:11:42,567 --> 00:11:44,567
I'm still worried about her.

219
00:11:44,567 --> 00:11:46,100
How are the kids
in the community?

220
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:48,533
[LAUGHS] You know
what they're like!

221
00:11:48,533 --> 00:11:51,633
They kept playing
after our painting sessions.

222
00:11:51,633 --> 00:11:53,767
Especially today,
since Edward was there.

223
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:55,067
They were all so playful!

224
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:02,533
- Oh.
- Umm.

225
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:05,000
Are you and Edward a thing?

226
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:09,567
[CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY] What?

227
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:11,967
[CHUCKLES] Oh, no!

228
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:14,100
Don't answer that.

229
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:16,533
[CLEARS THROAT]

230
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,567
Uh...

231
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Kiko.

232
00:12:22,133 --> 00:12:24,067
We're friends, aren't we?

233
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:27,600
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:29,100
Bffs.

235
00:12:32,900 --> 00:12:34,767
If...

236
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:37,100
you're asking if Edward
and I are dating...

237
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,967
the answer is no.
But if...

238
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:42,400
you're asking
if he's courting...

239
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:44,967
[CLEAR THROAT]

240
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:47,400
he is.

241
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:54,367
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

242
00:12:55,600 --> 00:12:57,100
[JADE] K-Kiko.

243
00:12:57,100 --> 00:12:59,133
[CHUCKLES] Oh, sure!

244
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:01,900
There's nothing wrong with that.

245
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,033
Edward is a nice guy, right?

246
00:13:08,067 --> 00:13:11,833
I don't see any reason not
to entertain him either.

247
00:13:18,767 --> 00:13:19,833
I mean...

248
00:13:19,833 --> 00:13:22,767
I know you and Edward
got off the wrong foot,

249
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,033
so if it's not fine
with you, Kiko--

250
00:13:25,033 --> 00:13:27,000
No, no, I'm okay.

251
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:30,067
Thank you, because...

252
00:13:31,133 --> 00:13:33,200
you're open about
these things with me.

253
00:13:34,667 --> 00:13:37,567
But, Jade, if you're happy,
then I am too.

254
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,500
Really?

255
00:13:42,033 --> 00:13:43,567
Absolutely.

256
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:46,133
Whatever happens...

257
00:13:47,767 --> 00:13:49,800
we'll still be friends.

258
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,500
Thank you.

259
00:13:54,500 --> 00:14:01,500
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

260
00:14:02,033 --> 00:14:03,467
Uh...

261
00:14:04,167 --> 00:14:06,600
I'll go ahead
and look for my sister.

262
00:14:06,967 --> 00:14:08,900
- Alright.
- Okay. Take care.

263
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:15,867
[MELANCHOLIC MUSIC CONTINUES]

264
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,100
I just have a lot on my mind.

265
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,700
The business's dad left.

266
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:29,867
My siblings.

267
00:14:31,267 --> 00:14:33,100
It all just piled up
at the same time.

268
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,533
But,

269
00:14:35,133 --> 00:14:36,533
I'm okay.

270
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:39,200
You?

271
00:14:40,733 --> 00:14:42,900
[MARTIN] I don't know
if I should tell you this.

272
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:45,667
But Uncle Ronald,

273
00:14:46,533 --> 00:14:49,533
he doesn't want to invest
in the hotel with Uncle Andy.

274
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:52,133
In other words,
he's asking us to choose.

275
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,967
What did you think?

276
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:56,933
I'm also torn.

277
00:14:56,933 --> 00:15:01,033
We don't want us to fight
just because of this.

278
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:03,300
Especially Luna.

279
00:15:04,233 --> 00:15:06,000
But the bottom line is?

280
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:09,300
I trust Uncle Ronald more.

281
00:15:10,233 --> 00:15:11,867
Okay.

282
00:15:11,867 --> 00:15:13,633
Then we'll go with Uncle Ronald.

283
00:15:14,100 --> 00:15:15,600
Leon.

284
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:17,733
If you can't
convince Luna,

285
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:19,600
then at least I'm on your side.

286
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:24,733
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:15:24,733 --> 00:15:26,700
I have to go, bro.
Let's talk again soon.

288
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:28,600
Okay. Take care.

289
00:15:28,600 --> 00:15:33,833
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

290
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,667
This isn't Juan.

291
00:15:36,167 --> 00:15:38,000
All the Juan Solimans here,
it's not him.

292
00:15:43,133 --> 00:15:45,700
Maybe he used
a different name...

293
00:15:45,833 --> 00:15:46,900
Nauj Namilos.

294
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:49,367
[BOTH LAUGHING]

295
00:15:50,667 --> 00:15:51,733
What?

296
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,533
It's just Juan Soliman
spelled backwards.

297
00:15:56,667 --> 00:15:57,833
Nauj Namilos.

298
00:15:57,967 --> 00:15:59,600
[CHUCKLING]

299
00:15:59,733 --> 00:16:00,867
You're so slow.

300
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:01,967
Come on.

301
00:16:02,100 --> 00:16:03,367
Wow, sorry.

302
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,800
You're pretty, but you're slow.

303
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:10,133
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:12,133
I'm getting tired, guys.

305
00:16:15,100 --> 00:16:16,167
Well...

306
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,333
That's just how it is.
We're all tired here.

307
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:21,100
That's why this really needs
to lead somewhere, right?

308
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:24,767
You know,
if Juan ever shows up,

309
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,767
I won't let that chance go
without

310
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:27,933
having him on my podcast.

311
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,167
I feel like that would be
the peak of my podcast

312
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:32,533
and my career, if I ever get
to interview him.

313
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:34,433
What would you even ask him?

314
00:16:34,833 --> 00:16:35,933
A lot!

315
00:16:36,067 --> 00:16:38,367
I could ask about his life.

316
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:41,433
How he was kidnapped.

317
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,267
Or about his father.

318
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:47,533
Or maybe we could unlock
things we don't know yet, right?

319
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:50,767
Hey.

320
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:53,000
You can back out if you don't
want this anymore.

321
00:16:53,133 --> 00:16:55,033
I was supposed to do this
alone anyway.

322
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:56,767
You all just got dragged
into it.

323
00:16:59,933 --> 00:17:01,300
Justin.

324
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,200
I already started this.

325
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:07,267
And once I start something,
I don't stop until I finish it.

326
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,767
That's it?

327
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:13,933
[CHUCKLES]

328
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:17,433
Of course, I want to help you.

329
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,667
There you go!

330
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,833
[CHUCKLES]

331
00:17:20,967 --> 00:17:22,433
What about the bar?

332
00:17:22,967 --> 00:17:24,733
I won't stop you anymore.

333
00:17:24,867 --> 00:17:26,767
If that's really what you want.

334
00:17:28,500 --> 00:17:30,300
I'll think about the bar later.

335
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:33,933
I'm actually enjoying
this adventure of ours.

336
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:36,833
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

337
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,367
Aw!

338
00:17:38,500 --> 00:17:39,733
Mhm!

339
00:17:39,867 --> 00:17:42,267
[CHUCKLES]

340
00:17:44,667 --> 00:17:45,900
[CLEARS THROAT]

341
00:17:46,367 --> 00:17:48,600
Anyway, I'll just get
some fresh air.

342
00:17:48,767 --> 00:17:49,800
Wait here.

343
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:18,133
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

344
00:18:34,233 --> 00:18:36,800
<i>Critically injured and
rushed to the hospital?</i>

345
00:18:38,967 --> 00:18:45,800
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

346
00:19:01,867 --> 00:19:02,833
Thank you.

347
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:04,867
For what?

348
00:19:05,733 --> 00:19:07,300
For coming with me
and Cheska,

349
00:19:07,433 --> 00:19:09,000
even though it was dangerous.

350
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:11,967
Well, we were all together
when that happened.

351
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:14,567
And of course,
I wanted to help you.

352
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,100
[SCOFFS]

353
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,100
Didn't you say you were scared?

354
00:19:19,600 --> 00:19:21,400
I still remember your face then.

355
00:19:23,567 --> 00:19:27,033
Or did you cry because
I shouted?

356
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,633
Because you got scared of me?

357
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:29,833
[SCOFFS]

358
00:19:29,967 --> 00:19:31,367
Me? Scared of you?

359
00:19:31,500 --> 00:19:33,167
- With that face of yours?
- [SCOFFS]

360
00:19:33,300 --> 00:19:35,167
- Oh, come on.
- I know I look good.

361
00:19:35,600 --> 00:19:37,267
But what if I do this?

362
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,400
- [LAUGHS]
- Scary, right?

363
00:19:39,533 --> 00:19:41,133
- No!
- This is the first time

364
00:19:41,267 --> 00:19:42,933
- I've made you laugh.
- Huh?

365
00:19:43,067 --> 00:19:44,133
- Yeah.
- Really?

366
00:19:44,267 --> 00:19:45,900
- Yeah.
- [CHUCKLING]

367
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:51,700
There! That was your face
when you got scared before.

368
00:19:53,033 --> 00:19:54,633
- Justin, Justin, look.
- What?

369
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:55,967
Look, look, look.

370
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:59,833
That guy. Isn't he one
of those who took Juan?

371
00:20:00,733 --> 00:20:01,467
Right?

372
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:03,400
He's the one we saw
at the precinct.

373
00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:08,633
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

374
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:09,767
Cheska!

375
00:20:15,500 --> 00:20:16,700
[CHESKA] Your phone.

376
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:19,400
- Why?
- Slow down.

377
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,233
[CHESKA] Why?

378
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:23,567
[TRIXIE] Why?

379
00:20:25,900 --> 00:20:27,033
Are you sure?

380
00:20:27,667 --> 00:20:29,767
I saw Uncle Andy on the phone.

381
00:20:29,900 --> 00:20:31,233
I heard his voice.

382
00:20:31,367 --> 00:20:32,567
I know it's him.

383
00:20:32,700 --> 00:20:34,967
You need to throw
that phone away.

384
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:36,700
And why would I do that?

385
00:20:36,867 --> 00:20:40,400
If you still value your life,
you'll do what I say.

386
00:20:40,533 --> 00:20:42,300
He won't stop going after you.

387
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:43,600
No.

388
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:46,767
This is the only evidence
I have against him.

389
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:48,867
This is the only proof that
he has a connection

390
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,033
to Sandro Soliman.

391
00:20:50,167 --> 00:20:51,600
You're really stubborn.

392
00:20:51,733 --> 00:20:53,667
Your life is already in danger!

393
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:54,833
He's dangerous!

394
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:58,000
What if Uncle Andy
was the one who had

395
00:20:58,133 --> 00:20:59,367
Dad and Uncle Michael killed?

396
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:02,100
I wouldn't be surprised
now that we know

397
00:21:02,233 --> 00:21:03,967
he's connected to Sandro.

398
00:21:05,233 --> 00:21:08,367
Then I need protection.

399
00:21:08,933 --> 00:21:11,167
I'm going to tell the police
everything I found out.

400
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:12,933
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

401
00:21:13,267 --> 00:21:14,367
So, what's this?
You're just informing me?

402
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,000
From the looks of it,

403
00:21:16,133 --> 00:21:16,933
you seem to have
made a decision already.

404
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,400
That's not it, Luna.

405
00:21:18,533 --> 00:21:20,367
We're weighing the pros
and cons here.

406
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:21,467
Fine.

407
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:23,933
Let's deal with the facts.
Lay it out, I'll listen.

408
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:27,167
Martin's investor
doesn't want to share.

409
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,267
[LUNA] And?

410
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:31,333
For me, Uncle Ronald
is the better choice.

411
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:34,267
He's more stable,
better capitalized, and--

412
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:35,367
No!

413
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,167
Uncle Andy will be
a stronger partner.

414
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:40,267
He lives here on the island.

415
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:42,533
He knows better
how businesses operate here.

416
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:44,367
And Uncle Ronald
has learned all of it.

417
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,633
Uncle Andy doesn't want
to have a partner

418
00:21:46,767 --> 00:21:48,200
if he's going to invest.

419
00:21:48,333 --> 00:21:50,433
If we had to choose,
it should be Uncle Andy.

420
00:21:51,367 --> 00:21:52,733
Have I mentioned
that he already paid off

421
00:21:52,867 --> 00:21:53,867
our debt to the bank.

422
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,200
What?!

423
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:56,933
You heard me.

424
00:21:57,367 --> 00:21:59,500
So if we had to choose,
we should pick Uncle Andy.

425
00:22:00,167 --> 00:22:01,733
We don't have a choice.

426
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:03,167
Unless you can pay him.

427
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:04,733
Because I can't.

428
00:22:09,567 --> 00:22:10,533
Luna, wait.

429
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,200
[GIO] Luna!

430
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:13,900
[SMACKS TABLE]

431
00:22:14,033 --> 00:22:20,333
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

432
00:22:27,567 --> 00:22:29,733
If you're going to convince me
about your investors--

433
00:22:29,867 --> 00:22:30,733
Let's go.

434
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:34,133
What?

435
00:22:34,267 --> 00:22:35,633
I said let's go somewhere.

436
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:38,367
Where are you going to take me?

437
00:22:39,500 --> 00:22:41,167
We're not going to talk
about investors, but...

438
00:22:41,300 --> 00:22:42,333
we're going somewhere.

439
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:49,533
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

440
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:53,900
Just trust me on this one.

441
00:22:57,267 --> 00:22:58,433
Okay?

442
00:23:05,600 --> 00:23:06,467
Okay.

443
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:08,367
Let's go.

444
00:23:23,500 --> 00:23:30,600
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

445
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:37,100
[LEON] Sir Henri!

446
00:23:37,233 --> 00:23:38,500
[HENRI] Oh, Mr. Almazan.

447
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,433
Do you have anything to report?

448
00:23:40,567 --> 00:23:47,567
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

449
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:52,767
<i> A big "thank you."</i>

450
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,167
<i>Ladies and gentlemen, and
everything in between,</i>

451
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:56,367
<i> under the ocean,</i>

452
00:23:56,533 --> 00:23:58,400
<i> we have a situationship.</i>

453
00:23:58,533 --> 00:23:59,933
<i> They were really close, bro.</i>

454
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:04,367
<i> They were almost kissing.</i>

455
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:06,067
<i>I'm looking for Sari.
Is she here?</i>

456
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,900
<i> Sari is Martin's girlfriend.</i>

457
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,933
<i>We can't let Uncle Andy
get into the hotel</i>

458
00:24:11,067 --> 00:24:12,200
<i> by any means.</i>

459
00:24:12,333 --> 00:24:13,500
<i> Tell me.</i>

460
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:15,933
<i>What's with Uncle Andy
for you to act like that?</i>

461
00:24:16,067 --> 00:24:18,233
<i>In case you forgot, seven
of us own the hotel,</i>

462
00:24:18,367 --> 00:24:20,233
<i>so you can't just keep
the information from us!</i>

463
00:24:20,367 --> 00:24:21,600
<i> Let's see who wins, Leon.</i>

464
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:23,567
<i> If I can't do it legally,</i>

465
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,000
<i>then I'll have to use
some violence.</i>

466
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:27,100
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [GRUNTS]

467
00:24:27,233 --> 00:24:28,700
- [BLOWS LAND]
- [GRUNTS]

468
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:29,933
[SCREAMS]

469
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:31,033
<i> Jade, what's wrong?</i>

470
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:32,567
<i> - There's a dead body!
</i>- [GASPS]

471
00:24:32,700 --> 00:24:34,300
<i> Kiko, there's a dead body!</i>
